 start their own sewing shop","imageAlt":"Mothers Diana Gualteros, 33 and Lucelly Foreno, 44 have taken advantage of the emerald mining resurgence to start their own sewing shop","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fa57.foxnews.com\u002Fstatic.foxnews.com\u002Ffoxnews.com\u002Fcontent\u002Fuploads\u002F2018\u002F10\u002F640\u002F320\u002Fmine4.jpg?ve=1&tl=1","copyright":"Fox News\u002FHollie McKay","source":"","isSpotlight":false,"responsiveImages":[{"media":"(max-width: 767px)","srcset":"https:\u002F\u002Fa57.foxnews.com\u002Fstatic.foxnews.com\u002Ffoxnews.com\u002Fcontent\u002Fuploads\u002F2018\u002F10\u002F1470\u002F828\u002Fmine4.jpg?ve=1&tl=1 2x"},{"media":"(min-width: 767px)","srcset":"https:\u002F\u002Fa57.foxnews.com\u002Fstatic.foxnews.com\u002Ffoxnews.com\u002Fcontent\u002Fuploads\u002F2018\u002F10\u002F1862\u002F1048\u002Fmine4.jpg?ve=1&tl=1 2x"}]}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"Seamstress and mother Diana Gualteros, 33, who opened a tailor shop, said she was given a head start with the task to sew uniforms for the miners. She just received her first request to start making school uniforms for village students."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"While locals often receive start-up support from outside companies like Fura who come in, the idea is for them to be &#x201C;self-sustaining,&#x201D; and develop contracts and business agreements that have the potential to long outlast the mining."}},{"is":"paragraph","props":{"text":"For most, it has been a baptism by fire &#x2013; even just the basics of opening a bank account and book-keeping in the remote region has been a change, albeit a welcome one."}},{"is":"article-image","props":{"type":"inline","caption":"Maria Porras, a 44-year-old mother of six and emerald mine wash plant worker","imageAlt":"Maria Porras, a 44-year-old mother of six and emerald mine wash plant worker","url":"https:\u002F\u002Fa57.foxnews.com\u002Fstatic.foxnews.com\u002Ffoxnews.com\u002Fcontent\u002Fuploads\u002F2018\u002F10\u002F640\u00